inn1.comm: good length ball on off stump, a hint of swing back into Gilchrist who covers the line and defends
fullish length again, bending back into the left-hander, Gilchrist plays it back to the bowler
short of  a length outside off stump, it cuts back into Gilchrist off the pitch, played to point on the back foot
pitches outside off stump on a good length and angles away from Gilchrist who lets it go through to McCullum
short of  a length outside off stump, the bounce is good from Mills and Gilchrist shoulders arms again
good length ball on leg and middle, Gilchrist moves back and across and plays it to midwicket
short of a length ball on leg stump, angling across the left-hander, Hayden plays back and defends

dropped! Vettroi grasses a simple chance at mid-off, Hayden planted his foot forward and drove on the up, he couldn't keep it down and hit it in the air to Vettori who dove to his right and fluffed it
defended back down the pitch on the front foot
full ball on off and middle stump, Hayden tries to drive but gets a leading edge to Vettori
Gillespie asks the question but Asad Rauf says not out, that pitched just outside off stump, Hayden lets it go but the ball cuts back and hits him on the pad, it was a touch too high
driven back to the bowler on the front foot
Australia are away, Mills sprays that wide outside off stump, Taufel says it's too wide
first runs off the bat, Gilchrist waits on the back foot and drives powerfully on the up through cover, it beats the infield and screams to the fence
short of  alength outside off stump, Gilchrist plays back, gets on top of the bounce and defends to point
that bounces a bit extra from a good length, Gilchrist takes his bottom hand off the handle and blocks it on the back foot
good length ball outside off stump, Gilchrist moves back and drives to point
short of  alength ball outside off stump and slanting away from Gilchrist who watches it through to the keeper
short of a length ball outside off, Gilchrist tries to cut but doesn't time it well, he hits it to short cover
Hayden gets off the mark by flicking a ball off his pads wide of the fielder at mid-on, he's timed that nicely and will get two
short ball down leg side, Hayden tries to pull but misses, the ball swings sharply away down leg side and beats McCullum too
short of a length ball on the hips, Hayden tucks it behind square leg for a single
full ball on middle stump, Gilchrist plays back and drives back to Gillespie
another huge wide down leg side, Gillespie pitches that outside leg stump and the ball swings further away, McCullum dives desperately to his right but isn't even close to it
short and wide outside off stump, Gilchrist cuts it in the air down to third man for one
defended to covers on the front foot
good length on off stump, Hayden gets into an awkward position with both feet close together and drives to mid-on
short and wide outside off stump, Gilchrist chases it and tries to play the upper cut, the umpire calls it wide, that was a bit harsh on Mills
fuller length outside off stump, Gilchrist gets on the front foot and mis-times the drive to mid-off
good length ball on off stump and swinging back into Gilchrist who closes the face of the bat and defends to midwicket
short of a length ball just outside off stump, Gilchrist gets on the back foot and powers it over cover for four, that looked risky but he smashed it really well
beaten outside the off stump, Mills comes back well
full ball outside off stump, Gilchrist frees his arms and lashes it through covers for four more

caught, and a sharp catch too! That was full again outside off stump, Gilchrist gave it a fearsome whack, hit with raw power, but he didn't get the elevation, Jeetan Patel moved a few steps to his left at mid-off and took the catch just above his head
a touch too short on middle stump, Hayden swings it away through square leg, that wasn't timed well
pitches full and wide outside off stump, Ponting gets his front foot forward and lets it go
hits a good length and line outside off stump, Ponting shoulders arms again
defended towards point on the front foot
good length ball on off stump, Ponting moves forward and towards the ball and defends to point
good ball to finish the over, on a good length and angling into Ponting's off stump, he plays it to cover on the front foot
left alone outside off stump

Hayden gets another life, he miscued the pull shot from outside off stump, Taylor is at midwicket and Vettori is at mid-on, both move towards the steepling chance, Taylor, running backwards, calls for it in the end and doesn't even get close to it
left alone outside the off stump
short of a length ball on the pads, whipped in the air through square leg for one
too short again this time hayden connects well with the pull shot and sends it racing to the midwicket fence
good length ball on off stump, Hayden gets forward and drives to mid off
Gillespie finds a good length outside off stump, Ponting lets it go to McCullum
short of a length outside off stump, Ponting drives to cover but doesn't time it well
good ball on off stump, had Ponting in two minds, whether to go forward or back, he ends up pushing at it and gets an edge down to third man
fullish ball on off and middle, Hayden steps down the pitch and hits it between midwicket and square leg for four
fullish length on off stump, Hayden tries to drive to cover but inside-edges it to midwicket
Gillespie tests Hayden with the short ball, Hayden pulls but not convincingly and gets two down to fine leg
superb shot from Ponting, too full from Mills and Ponting gets forward and drives it with a straight bat past Patel at mid-on, he's timed that impeccably
good length ball angling into Ponting's off and middle stump, he gets back and across and defends
Ponting was in a spot of bother with that, Mills cut the ball back into him from outside off stump, Ponting gets an inside edge and the ball gets stuck in the top of the pad
defended to midwicket on the front foot
full ball on off stump, Ponting leans across and drives wide of Patel at mid-on for one
pitches on a good length outside off stump, Hayden gets his foot forward and outside off and lets it go
short and wide outside off stump, that's too easy for Ponting who transfers weight on the front foot and cuts hard through point
Oram drops it short again on off and middle, Ponting swivels and pulls in front of midwicket, he hasn't timed it well enough to get four, they settle for three
pitches on a good length and angles into Hayden, he tries to play it to midwicket but gets hit on the thigh
fullish length from Oram, Hayden walks down and lofts with sheer power, that was all bottom hand, over mid-on for four runs
defended to covers on the front foot
Hayden walks down again but Oram drops it on a good length, he ends up dabbing it in front of point for a single
good length ball angling into Hayden from over the wicket, Hayden flicks uppishly to midwicket
strays down leg side, wide called
pitches outside off stump and turns quite a bit back into Hayden who plays back and dabs it to point for one
lots of turn on offer, Vettori pitches that outside of fstump and spins away, Ponting reaches out for it and defends to cover
cut past point on the back foot for a single
pushed through quickly outside of stump, Hayden gets his pad outside the line and pads it away

Hayden tries to sweep and gets a thick bottom edge and the ball bounces into the ground and then balloons up off the pad, McCullum catches it and the New Zealanders appeal, Umpire Taufel asks for the third umpire and he rules it not out, that hit ground just before hitting the pad
fuller delivery, played back to Patel
arm ball, Ponting pushes forward and gets beaten
comes forward and defends to the on side
quicker delivery on the off stump line, played to square leg
comes forward and drives wide of cover for a single
pushes off the back foot back down the track to Patel
comes forward and defends to the off side
good drift from Vettori, looking to play to the on side gets a leading edge to thirdman
defended on the front foot to cover
short ball bit quicker, cut off the back foot to deep backward-point
comes forward and defends to cover
tossed up outside the off stump, driven to mid off
a touch short, cut to cover, Taylor does well diving to his left
driven to mid on for a single
comes forward and defends, inside edge onto the pads and then rolls along to the off side
tossed up bit fuller, driven down the ground to long on
cuts off the back foot, Taylor at extra-cover misfields
cuts off the back foot to deep backward-point to pick up couple of runs
moves forward and pushes to the on side
works to midwicket
moves back and works to the on side
driven down the ground to long on to pick up a single
on the leg stump line, driven down the ground to long on
nicely tossed up delivery on the good length, comes forward and defends to short midwicket
comes forward and works to the on side
comes down the track and looks to drive down the ground, mishits it slightly in the air to deep mid on for a single
played to the on side
sweeps and misses, off the pad to the off side
swept down to fine leg for a single
short of a len gth outside off stump, Ponting cuts down to third man for two
a touch short on off and middle stump, Hayden plays back and forces it to long-on for a single
turned behind square for one
driven back to the bowler on the front foot
tossed up on off and middle, Hayden comes down the track and defends
good length ball on off stump and turning into Hayden who plays  it to midwicket
a touch shorter on off stump, Hayden goes right back and works it off his pads to midwicket
drifting on to middle and leg stump, Ponting moves across and flicks it off his pads
tossed up on off stump, Hayden tries to sweep and gets a top edge that lobs behind square leg
full toss angling into leg stump, Hayden pushes it to long- on for a single
good length outside off stump, Ponting reaches out for it and flicks it in the air through midwicket
pitching outside off stump and turning away from Hayden who gets a thick outside edge to point
short and wide outside off stump, Hayden rocks back and cuts through the cover point region
defended back to the bowler on the front foot
played to midwicket on the back foot
tossed up on off and middle, Hayden steps down and smothers the spin and dabs it to mid-on for one
pushed flat through the air on off and middle, Ponting plays forward and pushes it to point, Hayden sets off for the single but  Ponting sends him back
defended to midwicket on the front foot
floated through the air on off stump, Ponting lunges forward and has to wait for the ball to come to him, he angles it towards point with the open face of the bat
Ponting plays forward again and tries to defend, he gets an inside edge to midwicket
cut to short third man on the back foot
fullish length outside off stump, Ponting goes on the front foot and square drives through point

pitches outside off stump and turning away from Hayden, Patel bowled that a bit quicker and Hayden used the pace to guide it down to third man, Ponting  wanted the third but slipped after he completed the single
swept fine down to fine leg for four, Hayden didn't connect that perfectly but he got it fine enough, that's the first boundary in ten overs
pushed to mid-on off the front foot
good length ball on middle stump, Hayden plays back and defends on the leg side
short of  a length ball pitching on middle and off and angling away from Hayden who runs it down to third man
good length ball on off stump, Ponting pushes it off the front foot to Vincent at point, he doesn't collect it cleanly and Hayden calls Ponting through for the single
tight line and length on off stump, Hayden dabs it into the covers for another quick single, Australia bring up their 100
defended to cover on the front foot

full ball on off stump, Ponting moves across and falls over a touch, he gets an outside edge to point, Hayden sets off for the single but changes his mind and runs back, just three runs of that Powerplay over.

pitches on a good length outside off stump, Hayden tires to muscle it through midwicket by stepping down the track, Taylor scampers across, picks up and tries to run ot Ponting at the non-striker's end
pushed to midwicket on the front foot
how lucky is Hayden today! Oram bangs one short, Hayden goes down on one knee and tries to slog-pull/sweep it, he gets a top edge over short fine leg
short of a length ball, Hayden gets on top of the balla nd steers it through gully for four to the third man fence, well-controlled shot that was
dropped short outside off stump, Hayden waits for it and cuts firmly but hits it to the man at point
good length ball on off stump, Hayden pushes to covers on the back foot
Gillespie drops it short, Ponting moves forward and pulls majestically over midwicket for four, top shot
good length ball outside off stump, Ponting lunges forward, opens the face and angles it to point
just short of a length on off and middle stump, Ponting defends back to the bowler
glorious shot, Ponting knew fine leg was in the circle, so he moved across to one that was full on the pads and flicked it in the air and down to the fine leg fence
short of a length ball on off stump, Ponting moves forward and plays it behind point and down to third man for a single
just a fraction short and Hayden moves back quickly and pulls through midwicket to retain strike, he moves on to 47
good length on off stump from Oram, Hayden blocks it back to the bowler
slower ball ends up as a full toss on off stump, Hayden drives to McMillan at long-on for a single
a fraction short, just a fraction and Ponting is so quick to rock back, swivel and pull to deep midwicket

that's Hayden's fifty! Oram drifted down leg side with his fine leg in the circle, Hayden pulls it wide of that man and collects four, he's  had a lot of luck but you got to make it count, Hayden's done that, well played
pulled in front of square this time, Oram is bowling far too short at his gentle pace
defended back to the bowler on the front foot
on a good length but too wide outside off stump, Hayden uses the width and runs it down to third man for a single
good length ball angling into Ponting rom outside off stump, played to point on the back foot

a touch too full and Ponting lunches on the front foot and lofts it over mid-on, he's timed that superbly for he hardly hit that with any effort, the ball bounces once before reaching the fence, that's the 100 partnership between these two
flicked off his pads in front of midwicket for two more
good length and straight, Ponting hammers the drive back at Gillespie who gets his boot in the way and saves a certain boundary
Ponting cuts on the front foot to Fulton at covers who misfields to allow the single, Ponting reaches fifty too, he's played a perfect innings, I can't remember his playing a false shot
a touch short outside off stump, Ponting plays it late to short third man, Hayden calls him through for a sharp single
bowled flat on off stump from round the wicket, Hayden plays it back to Patel
fuller length on middle stump, Hayden closes the face and works it through square leg
played to cover on the back foot, Ponting mis-timed that and he's not happy with himself
pushed to midwicket on the front foot
full ish length again, Ponting moves forward and plays it to midwicket
beats Hayden in the flight and Hayden cuts to backward point where a fumble allows him to come back for the second
flighted quicker through teh air, Hayden comes forward and drives back to Vettori
a touch short this time, Hayden pulls to deep backward square
defended to backward point on the front foot
fuller length on off stump, Ponting drives in the air but wide of cover
tossed up on off stump, Ponting plays forward with soft hands and drops it short on the off side for a single
Ponting takes a step down to Patel and flicks him through midwicket, a little in the air but there's no fielder there
shot! Hayden steps out to Patel, meets the ball on the bounce and lofts dead straight back over Patel's head, that was hit with so much power
driven uppishly just short of the man at cover
dabbed through midwicket on the front foot, there's huge gap there and they manage to run two
Patel drops it short and wide outside off stump, Hayden tries to cut but doesn't time it well
pitches on off stump and spins away from Hayden who moes across and closes the face to place it in that huge gap at midwicket, two more
flat ball outside off stump, Ponting waits on the back foot and cuts to deep point
blowed flat and fast on off and midde, Hayden plays back and defends to midwicket
full outside off stump, Hayden goes down on one knee and drives to cover
tossed up outside of stump, Hayden plays right back and cuts through point
tight line on off stump, Ponting gets forward and defends to cover
lovely ball, the flight drew Ponting forward, the ball pitched on off stump and Ponting was well and turly beaten perhaps for the first time in the innings, the ball spun past the outside edge
fullish length on off stump, Hayden drives to long-off for one
full again from McMillan on off stump, Ponting plays forward and drives to long-off
short of a length on middle and off, Hayden waits for it, comes forward and drives to long-on
Ponting punches down to long-off for one more, they are milking the singles off McMillan
full on the pads, Hayden punches down the ground to long-on again
112kmh on off and middle, Ponting moves across and drives to long-on, that's six singles off that over, all of them gown the ground
tossed up on middle and off, Ponting moves forward and pushes it past Vettori for  a single
dropped short and angling down leg side, Hayden whips it behind square for a single
full ball outside off stump, Ponting drives through cover on the front foot for a single
bowled short outside off stump and spinning back into Hayden who moves on the back foot and cuts in front of point for a single
tossed up on middle and off stump, Ponting plays an inside out chip shot over the fielder at cover, that looked dangerous but it was placed well
defended to covers on the front foot
wide outside off stump, cut down the third man
slips very wide down leg side, it beats McCullum and the batsmen run one too
pulled in the air wide off the fielder at midwicket, that wasn;t controlled at all by Hayden who took one hand off the bat
flicked off the pads behind square for one
Hayden tries to play a late cut but it was too close to him, he gets beaten
short and wide outside the off stump, Hayden moves back and cuts hard, he's timed and placed that really wella nd it beats the man on the fence at deep point
what's he doing?? Taylor pitched that outside off stump and turning away from Hayden who goes down on one knee and swats it down with an almost straight bat, curious shot
good length wide outside off stump, Ponting tries to cut but the length isn't right for the shot, he bottom edges it on the off side
good length just outside off stump and angling into Ponting who gets forward and defends back to Mills
full toss on off stump, Ponting drives down the ground for a single
good length ball on middle and off stump, Hayden comes down the track and yorks himself, digs it out back to Mills
dropped a touch short and Hayden pulls it away to deep square leg for one
fullish ball on off and middle, Ponting leans across and drives wide of the fielder at mid-on for one
tossed up on middle an leg, Ponting pushes it through midwicket and Hayden pushes him to run two runs, excellent running
worked off the pads behind square for one

dropped! Hayden swept that powerfully from outside of stump, he absolutely smashed that at Hamish Marshall at midwicket, he just couldn't hang on to the catch, Marshall is on the field as a substitute, that;s the third life Hayden has had, does he have six more?
swept to deep backward square for one
short and wide outside off stump, Hayden cuts to deep point
full ball on off and middle stump, Ponting drives down the ground for a single
full ball swinging back into Ponting's off stump, driven on the front foot to cover
full again just outside off stump, Ponting gives it a thump but hits it straight to mid-off
dropped a fraction short, Ponting goes down on one knee and pulls through midwicket, Fleming has protection in the deep
slower ball on good length on off stump and angling away from Hayden who tries to hit over cover, he gets a thick edge that clears the infield
well bowled, right up there in the blockhole, Ponting digs it out to mid-off
full again and on middle and leg stump, driven down the ground to long-on for a single
dropped a touch short, Ponting swivels and pulls down to deep square leg where Fleming has a man on the fence

McCullum is standing up to the stumps and he does a fantastic job of collecting one that bounced sharply outside the off stump, Ponting misses the cut and McCullum whips off the bails in a flash, Ponting just got his foot back in time
cut to point on the front foot
short outside the off stump, Ponting swings it away through midwicket on the back foot
excellent improvisation, Oram angles that into Hayden from round the wicket, trying to cramp hi for room, Hayden moves towards the leg side and cuts hard over the gully region for four runs
Oram bowls this just short of a length on off and middle, Hayden plays back and pulls to deep midwicket for a single to end the over
good ball nearly in Hayden's blockhole, he digs it out on the front foot back to the bowler
full ball on midle and off stump, Hayden biffs it down the ground, Vettori runs across from long-on and saves the four
the slower ball, Hayden tries to heave it over the off side but gets an outside edge that runs fine of the fielder at short third man, four more
smashed down the ground again, Vettori can;t save this one, four runs and Hayden is on 99

full ball on the pads, Hayden flicks it off the toes behind square for two runs, that's his hundred! He's had a lot of luck with three dropped catches, Vettori dropped him on 0 in fact, but well played Haydos!
shirt ball from Mills and Hayden loves it, he smashes that through midwicket for four more, he's switching into overdrive now
Ponting slashes hard outside the off stump, that was on a good length and Ponting's outside edge flies over short third man for four more, New Zealand are bleeding during this Powerplay
full ball on off stump, Ponting smashed that back at Oram, that was a catch in theory, only in theory mind yyou for it was hit extremely hard
Hayden's blazing hot now, Oram bowls that a touch too full and Hayden powers it through midwicket for four runs
full toss on off stump, Hayden makes room and bashes it wide off the fielder at mid-off for four more
another one sails away, Hayden picks that from a full length and whacks it down the ground just wide of the fielder at long-on, one-bounce four
defended on the off side, 17 from that over to follow the previous over that leaked 16
good length on off stump, Ponting reaches for it and drives to cover
flat ball on off stump, Ponting opens the face and runs it to point, they take a quick single to bring up the 200 partnership
full ball on off stump, Hayden backs away and slams it to covers, he was cramped for room, well bowled
bowled him! Hayden gave him the charge and was beaten by the flight, he missed his heave over the leg side and the ball rattled the off stump
excellent ball on off stump, tight line and length, Clarke drives back to Vettori
tossed up on off and middle, Clarke comes down the track and defends, what a brilliant over from Vettori
hits a good length outside off stump and spins back into Ponting, inducing an inside edge
defended on teh front foot back down the pitch
full ball on middle and leg stump, Ponting flicks through midwicket and Clarke, who's nice and fresh, runs two easily
flicked superbly off his pads and the placement is excellent to, fours runs to deep midwicket&
straight hit goes the distance, Ponting steps down and hammers Patel down the ground, the ball just clears the fence
drifts down leg side, wide called
full ball on middle and leg, Ponting drives down to long-on for one
dabbed with gentle hands into the massive gap at midwicket, Ponting, as tired as he is, races through for two runs
dabbed to short third man on the front foot, Clarke sprints through for a single
short and wide outside the off stump, Clarke cuts through point for one
full on the pads, Ponting pushes through midwicket for a single, he's on 99
full ball on off stump, Clarke pushes down the ground to long off for one
defended on the front foot to covers, Pontign stays on 99.
short ball on off and middle, Clarke rocks back and pulls powerfully to deep midwicket where Marshall does the fielding, two runs
Clarke uses his feet to step down the pitch and drive to long-on
full ball on the pads, Ponting nonchalantly flicks off his legs for a single behind square, he gets a rousing ovation from the crowd, a superb innings
flicked off the pads through the leg side for a quick double

caught at deep midwicket, Clarke tries to clear the midwicket boundary, he hits that really hard but doesn't get the necessary elevation, he picks out Hamish Marshall in the deep who takes the catch at knee height
Ponting clips it down to long-on for a single
cheeky but very effective, Ponting waits for the ball to nearly pass him before bring his bat down to play the late cut that runs fine to the third man fence
flicked off the pads for two runs behind square leg
driven down the ground to long-off for a single
good length ball on off stump, Symonds pushes to long-off for one
pushed into cover for a single
short of a length drifting on to the pads, Symonds plays it through midwicket for one
there she blows! Symonds gives Patel the charge and lofts him high high high over the long-on fence, that's a massive hit
chipped to long-off for one
Ponting works it down the ground for one more
full ball on off stump, driven to long-off for another single
full ball on the pads, Ponting tries to paddle it fine but hits it to short fine leg
full ball on leg stump, Ponting drives to long-on for one more, that's the end of Patel's spell
Ponting falls after a colossal innings, he pulls that from outside off stump and didn't connect as well as he would have liked, the ball soars high and straight to Fulton at deep midwicket
slower ball on middle stump, Symonds pushes that through midwicket and the batsmen run an easy two
brute force! Symnonds backs away and cross-bats it straight down the ground, thats a very flat six, awesome power from Symonds
he can be delicate too, Symonds tries to paddle sweep that but doesn't make contact
driven down the ground for a single
short of a length ball on middle stump, Hussey turns it off his pads for a single
good length angling into Hussey's off and middle stump, he gets a leading edge back to the bowler
full and wide down leg side, McCullum doesn;t collect it and the batsmen run one, wide called
Gillespie bounces Symonds outside the off stump, he flat bats it high over midwicket, he didn't connect that properly but the ball falls safe
Symonds tries to heave it over cover but gets a top-edge down to third man
full ball on the pads, Symonds moves away  to square leg and Gillespie follows him, played to midwicket for one
Hussey tries to hit it too hard down the ground, gets an inside edge on to pad for a single to the off side
bowled him with the yorker! Symonds makes room but moving away towards leg side, Gillespie fires in the yorker and Symonds misses it, the ball crashes into the stumps
full ball on middle and off, dug out into the covers
short of a length ball on middle and leg, White moves across and tries to tickle it to fine leg, the ball hits him on the thigh and they run a  leg bye
full ball on off stump, Hussey squeezes it to midwicket
full ball in the blockhole, Hussey plays it to covers, this is excellent bowling

full toss on off and middle, Hussey steps down and cross-bats it flat and down to long on, big Jacob Oram jumps up to try and catch it but the ball just hits the tip of his fingers and crosses the fence
played down to long-on for two more to end the over
drifting on to the pads, white moves across and gets hit on the thigh pad, another leg bye on the leg side
low and full on off stump, Hussey pushes it into covers for one
defended to midwicket on the front foot
short and wide outside the off stump, White biffs it through covers on the back foot for one
he over-steps, Hussey gets a inside edge on to his pad and they run a very sharp single with the ball very near the stumps
the yorker outside off stump, White defends it to cover, great ball from Gillespie

short ball and White gives it a mighty pull, Lou vincent runs to his left on the boundary and dives full length , the ball goes wide of his outstretched hand and bounces on the rope, it's signalled six!
White tries to heave it down the ground but gets an inside egde down to fine leg for four
pulled through midwicket for a single
what a shot! Hussey moves down the pitch and towards leg stump to make room and lofts it over extra cover, he's timed it brilliantly and it sails over the fence
the yorker to end the over, Hussey charges again and gets an inside edge back to the bowler
fullish length on off stump, white heaves it down the ground for two to long-on
full ball on off stump and White launches it over extra cover, that's an inside out shot and he gets three for his effort
that's his third six! Hussey swings that with the angle high and far over midwicket, that's a massive hit
full ball on off stump, Hussey drives down the ground for one
Gillespie bowls the yorker and White digs it out for  a single to point
full toss on off stump, Hussey flat-bats it down the ground, it's hit very straight and gets two runs

inn2.comm: New Zealand are away first ball, that was pitched on a good length on off and middle, Vincent drops it with gentle hands on the leg side for a quick single
drifts on to the pads, Fleming clips it down to fine leg for one
143kmh, in the channel outside off stump, Vincent gets his front foor forward and lets it go
short of a length ball angling into the hips, Vincent plays it down behind square on the leg side for one more
fullish length pitching outside off stump and angling away from Fleming who plays back and across and gets beaten
excellent ball to finish, pitching on a good length on off stump, Fleming plays back again and trusts the bounce enough to let it go over the top of off stump
pitches on a  good length outside off stump and slants away from the right-hander, Vincent lets it go
and again, this was pitched closer to off stump and Vincent shoulders arms again
short of a length ball on leg stump, Vincent pushes it off his hips behind square leg for a single
pitches wide outside off stump and swings wider away from the left hander, that's the first extra Australia have conceded
angling into leg stump and Fleming dabs it behind square on the leg side for a sharp single
short of a length on leg and middle, that stopped on Vincent who closed the face too early and got a leading edge that falls short of point
slower ball at 124kmh, Vincent fends at it outside the off stump and gets beaten
short ball outside off stump, Fleming drops his wrists and lets it go through to Gilchrist
good length ball on middle and off stump, Fleming plays it back to Lee on the back foot
full ball outside off stump, Fleming drives away from his body and gets a thick edge down to McGrath at third man
tight line and length on off stump at 146kmh, Vincent gets behind the line and defends to point
outstanding shot and a superb save prevents four, Vincent drives off the back foot and timed it really well, Symonds dives to his left at cover and fields with one hand, outstanding
dabbed wide of Symonds and they try to steal a single, Symonds sprints to his left picks up and shies at the batsman's end, Fleming was gone had he hit
good length ball pitching on off stump and moving away from Vincent who plays back and defends on the off side
